com.sri.ai.expresso.api

Interface SyntacticFunctionApplication

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, Comparable<Object>, Expression, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultSyntacticFunctionApplication

    @Beta
public interface SyntacticFunctionApplication
extends Expression
    An Expression that represents a syntactic function application (that is, something that takes expressions themselves, rather than their values, as arguments). A typical example is the syntactic expression "type", which denotes the type of its "argument": type(X) stands for the type of X, not the type of its value. This means that a syntactic function does not have sub-expressions, because sub-expressions are by definition expressions whose values are used in the definition of the interpretation of their parent expression.
    Author:
    braz
